      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ERUPT (7) crossed over from out wide last start before finishing second (30.37) at this track in a Grade 5 over 520m. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Makes plenty of appeal. ANCESTRAL QUEEN (6) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 6 lengths at Nowra in a handy 29.74 beating Zipping Chicago. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from six starts. Leading chance again. VALLEY CASH (5) broke from the inside draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only 1.5 lengths (29.76) behind Zipping Zeppelin at Richmond. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Racing well and deserves a win. CUMBRIA LAURA (2) has claims fresh from a recent placing.",
